Third BSE case confirmed in Japan
---------------------------------
A Holstein dairy cow born in Gunma prefecture and slaughtered in another
prefecture has been [found infected with BSE, the Health, Labor and
Welfare Ministry said Friday, 30 Nov. This third case of Bovine Spongiform
Encephalopathy (BSE) has been confirmed in Tokyo on Sunday, 2 Dec 2001 by a
ministry's panel of experts. All 3 BSE cows in Japan were born between
March and April 1996, and all 3 animals were given the same kind of powder
milk produced at the same factory in Gunma prefecture.
